quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  23,1,"The believers have indeed attained true success:"{1},footnotes:1:1
  23,2,"those who, in their Prayers, humble themselves;"{1}{2},footnotes:1:1,footnotes:2:2
  23,3,"who avoid whatever is vain and frivolous;"{1},footnotes:1:1
  23,4,"who observe Zakah;"{1},footnotes:1:1
  23,5,"who strictly guard their private parts"{1},footnotes:1:1
  23,6,"save from their wives, or those whom their right hands possess; for with regard to them they are free from blame ""
  23,7,"As for those who seek beyond that, they are transgressors""{1},footnotes:1:1
  23,8,"who are true to their trusts and their covenants,"{1},footnotes:1:1
  23,9,"and who guard their Prayers."{1},footnotes:1:1
  23,10,"Such are the inheritors"